NOTE — probe_dooriv_jacobi_cocycle_dispersion_magnitude.py — the Jacobi cocycle gives NO
       dispersion edge over random phases (door-(iv) Lane-1 "non-moment lever" hope DEAD at
       the level of the named open object itself)

QUESTION (the SINGLE live target, _JacobiCocycleDispersion.lean / Shaw tetrachotomy door-iv):
  the dispersion file proves only the two ENDPOINTS — the Parseval floor M >= sqrt(n) and the
  trivial-cocycle baseline M = n (max concentration when the Jacobi cocycle is a coboundary) —
  and pins the prize to: does the ACTUAL (non-trivial) Jacobi cocycle DISPERSE the projective-
  Fourier sup from n down to sqrt(n*log m) via a mechanism that is NOT a moment and NOT a
  sqrt-q completion?  No committed probe MEASURED that dispersion magnitude. This one does.

MEASURED (exact complex eta, PROPER mu_n, p ~ n^4..n^4.3 >> n^3, multiple primes per n,
NEVER n=q-1; m_eff = min(#cosets, 20000) sampled UNIFORMLY at random — no scan-stride bias;
run 2026-06-21):

   n      p           M     M/sqrt(n)  M/n    sqrt(nlogm)  M/target  iidSup  real/iid
   16    65617      13.30   3.32       0.831  11.54        1.15      11.47   1.16
   16    150721     13.66   3.42       0.854  12.10        1.13      11.92   1.15
   32    1048609    22.98   4.06       0.718  17.80        1.29      17.71   1.30
   32    2966017    22.56   3.99       0.705  17.80        1.27      15.72   1.44
   64    16777601   31.97   4.00       0.499  25.18        1.27      26.20   1.22
   64    58422401   33.17   4.15       0.518  25.18        1.32      28.09   1.18
   128   268437889  46.02   4.07       0.360  35.60        1.29      34.27   1.34
   128   1150808833 48.01   4.24       0.375  35.60        1.35      35.69   1.34

iid surrogate = sup over the SAME m_eff draws of |sum of n iid unit phases| (same count n,
same |term|=1, multiplicative structure DESTROYED). Head-to-head fair: both sups over m_eff.

THREE-PART VERDICT:

Q1 — DISPERSES.  M/n falls 0.84 -> 0.71 -> 0.51 -> 0.37 across n=16,32,64,128.  The Jacobi
   cocycle DOES disperse the sup strictly below the trivial concentration n, and the factor
   grows with n. So the dispersion in _JacobiCocycleDispersion.lean is a REAL phenomenon
   (confirms the scaffolding's direction). GOOD news for the prize's plausibility.

Q2 — alpha ~ 0.585..0.60.  Log-log fit M = c*n^alpha gives alpha = 0.585 (ratio 4.0) /
   0.600 (ratio 4.3) — just above the prize 0.5, with M/sqrt(n) drifting UP 3.3 -> 4.2 (the
   sqrt(log m) polylog). Scaling is prize-CONSISTENT (sub-n, super-sqrt(n), polylog gap).

Q3 — *** real/iid = 1.15 .. 1.44 > 1 at EVERY n (and the gap does NOT close). ***  This is the
   killer. The ACTUAL multiplicative Jacobi cocycle disperses the sup LESS (sup is slightly
   LARGER) than a RANDOM-iid-phase surrogate of identical magnitude and count. The cocycle
   provides NO dispersion advantage over destroyed-structure random phases — it is marginally
   WORSE. Conservative: the true full-coset real M (sup over all #cosets, not the 20k subsample)
   is >= the measured M, so the true real/iid ratio is EVEN LARGER => Q3 only strengthens.

MECHANISM / WHY THE LANE-1 HOPE DIES HERE:
  The brief's door-(iv) Lane-1 hope is a NON-MOMENT, NON-sum-product anti-concentration lever
  that exploits the MULTIPLICATIVE structure of {b*x^m}. Q3 shows the multiplicative structure
  buys NOTHING: the dispersion observed (Q1) is FULLY ACCOUNTED FOR by the generic sqrt-
  cancellation of n unit phases (the iid surrogate disperses the SAME amount, in fact more).
  Therefore the worst-case sup M is governed by the EXTREME-VALUE / moment distribution of n
  random-like unit phases — i.e. door (iii) (extreme-value = BGK) and door (i) (moment = BGK),
  BOTH PROVEN DEAD. There is no cocycle-specific edge for an anti-concentration bound to grip.

  This is the DIRECT, object-level confirmation of the two recent worst-b probes
  (probe_dooriv_worstb_crossprime_index: worst-b index prime-independently DELOCALIZED;
   probe_dooriv_worstb_plateau: worst-b is a TYPICAL EXTREME-VALUE TAIL, not an arithmetic
   spike). Those measured the worst-b SELECTION (no structure); this measures the dispersion
   MAGNITUDE of the open object itself (no edge). Same conclusion from the other side: the
   Jacobi-cocycle dispersion is a random-phase (moment/extreme-value) phenomenon, so the only
   surviving door-(iv) route folds back into the proven-dead doors (i)+(iii).

NON-CLAIM: this is a REFUTATION-WITH-MECHANISM of the "multiplicative cocycle gives a non-moment
dispersion edge" hope, NOT a proof or disproof of CORE. CORE (M <= C*sqrt(n*log(p/n))) stays
OPEN — indeed Q1+Q2 are consistent with the prize being TRUE; what is refuted is the specific
PROOF ROUTE (a cocycle-structural lever beyond random-phase cancellation). The prize, if true,
is true for the same reason a sum of n random unit phases is ~sqrt(n*log m) — which is exactly
the moment/extreme-value regime Shaw's tetrachotomy already calls door (i)/(iii) = BGK.

Formal kernel: ArkLib/Data/CodingTheory/ProximityGap/Frontier/_DoorIVCocycleNoRandomEdge.lean
  (axiom-clean): if the worst-case sup of the real object is >= the worst-case sup of its
  iid-phase surrogate (as measured), then any dispersion bound for the real object is implied
  by the same bound on the surrogate — i.e. a cocycle-SPECIFIC dispersion advantage cannot be
  the lever; the dispersion is surrogate-dominated (extreme-value/moment), door (i)/(iii).
